      "content": "it feels like you're just trying to put a bandaid on an existential wound. \"finding meaning\" sounds like just another way to distract ourselves from the truth. if we're just biological accidents, wouldn't the most logical thing to do be to just stop? to stop the struggle and accept the void instead of fighting it so hard? it almost feels like we're being irrational by clinging to a life that has no objective value.",
